==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impeyan pheasant
<hw>Im"pey*an pheas"ant</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m"p⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧n
f⟦ecr⟧z"⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>. <ety>[From Lady <etsep>Impey</etsep>, who
attempted to naturalize the bird in England.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An Indian crested pheasant of the genus <gen>Lophophorus</gen>.
Several species are known. Called also <altname>monaul</altname>,
<altname>monal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They are remarkable for the bright color and brilliant
matallic hues of their plumage. The best known species (<spn>Lophophorus
Impeyanus</spn>) has the neck of a brilliant metallic red, changing to
golden yellow in certain lights.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imphee</ent>⟦br⟧
